employing a variety of animal species is listed in Table 1 to illustrate the types of fertilization studies that have been undertaken using confocal microscopy, and as a launching point toward obtaining further information regarding specimen preparation approaches for specific species. In this chapter, methods to prepare sea urchin eggs and embryos for immunochemical confocal studies of cytoskeletal organization are described. 2. Materials 2.1. Equipment and Supplies
1. A dozen 50-mL beakers, a half dozen 300- and 600-mL glass beakers, and a few 1- and 2-L beakers.

