completed. (E,F) Control (non-CIPC-treated) zygotes subjected to Triton X-100/glycerol extraction prior to fixation in cold methanol. Routine epifluorescence microscopy. (E) Metaphase; (F) anaphase. Note the distortion of the microtubule cytoskeleton in the anaphase spindle (compare with Fig. 2F). The metaphase spindle in this example is very well preserved for extracted specimens; frequently, detectable physical distortion occurs in this stage, as well as all others, following extraction. (A–D) Double labeled with E7 anti-β-tubulin antibody and Hoechst; arrows indicate chromatin.

